<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80A51377D6AFDEA3EA4FEB2" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80A51377D6AFDEA3EA4FEB2" blockId="10.[828,1437,574,725]" lastBlockId="11.[151,761,190,437]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80A51367D6AFDEA3CFFFDB2" bold="true" box="[828,958,574,597]" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E80A51367D90FDEA3BCBFDB2" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2012" box="[966,1162,574,597]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linae">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80A51367D90FDEA3BCBFDB2" box="[966,1162,574,597]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Pselaphodes linae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80A51367D22FD8A3C80FD92" box="[884,961,606,629]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Hainan</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49BC4499E80A51367DA7FD8A3B79FD92" box="[1009,1080,606,629]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Fujian</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80A51367AF6FD8A3B9EFD92" box="[1184,1247,606,629]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">China</collectingCountry>
and later reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80A51367D21FDAA3C88FD72" box="[887,969,638,661]" name="Taiwan" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. Here it is recorded from northern 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80A51367B14FDAA3ADDFD72" box="[1346,1436,638,661]" name="Vietnam" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
for the first time. This species is readily recognizable by the deeply emarginate ventral and lateral surfaces of antennomeres 11 and 10, respectively, presence of a highly raised disc-like projection near the apex of antennomere 9, and metatibia with an acute tooth at apical 1/3. The male from 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80B51377E99FECA3E68FED2" box="[207,297,286,309]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
shows little morphological variation in both external features and aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF07DAF3E80A51367EC1F8083ADCF7C3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5037484" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5037484" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5037484/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" startId="10.[151,182,2012,2031]" targetBox="[278,1317,764,1991]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80A51367EC1F8083ADCF7C3" blockId="10.[151,1437,2012,2084]" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 8. Male diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E80A51367FE9F8083D2FF808" authority="Yin &amp; Li, 2021" authorityName="Yin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[447,622,2012,2031]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jendeki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E80A51367FE9F8083D2FF808" box="[447,622,2012,2031]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Pselaphodes jendeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23FEB12E80A51367C24F8083DF4F808" box="[626,693,2012,2031]" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
A – left antennal club, in dorsal view; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; F – apex of mesotibia; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite 7 (IX); I–E – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (E) view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm in A, B, D, E, G; 0.2 mm in C, I, J, E; 0.1 mm in H; 0.05 mm in F.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80B51377EC1FE8A3EE0FE52" pageId="11" pageNumber="46" type="distribution">
